args:
Ciella arrives in Alberia and learns of rumors
spreading around the kingdom that the prince
has been possessed by the Other. But Ayaha
and Otoha have followed Ciella, and they soon
make for the Halidom with sights set on Laxi.
Transition to search mode completed.\nCommencing scan for nearby enemies.
Scan completed. No enemies detected.\n▷Phew! Guess we're safe for now.◁
What going on, you two? You've been\nstrangely cautious about our surroundings\never since we left the Halidom.
▷Er, well, actually...◁\nI predict an attack from the twins,\nand therefore remain on alert.
You're talking about those kids\nAyaha and Otoha from Agito?
▷Yeah, the ones who hate me and Laxi.◁\nI observed excessive hostility towards us\non their part in our last confrontation.
▷We haven't seen them in a while,\nbut I doubt they're just backing off.◁\nHence the need for vigilance.
You're not wrong that those Agito folk\nare a real bothersome bunch.

▷You can say that again. I mean,
I hope nothing happens, but still...◁
There can be no carelessness here.
We must continue searching for enemies.
Oy, check this! I hear the seventh scion\nis actually the Other!
That would certainly explain many of the\nodd things that have been happening...
See?! I TOLD you Ciella was here!
Yeah, yeah—but did you catch\nthose stories about the Other?
I knew she was hiding something...\nLet's chase her down and find out what!
(Doubtless the Ilian Church is working\nbehind the scenes to seed these rumors.)
(Of course, the only ones who gain by\nmaking the southern Church fight with the\nroyal family is the northern Church.)
(And supposing that's true, it must be\nthat man pulling the strings...)
I knew I was being followed.\nWhat are you two doing here?
You looked like you were up to something\nfun and exciting, and we want in!
You came here to play around with the\nfake prince, didn't you?!
You were all serious, like ＂they've started\nto move, so I'm going south,＂ but you can't\nfool us! Isn't that right, Aya?
That's right! We can't be fooled!\nNow fess up already!
We won't let you sneak out and have all\nthe fun without us—we wanna rip that\nmechanical puppet apart!
You're not wrong that it's something fun,\nfor rumors regarding the prince are\nspreading across the entire land.
Folks everywhere are whispering that he\nwent and got possessed by the Other.
You two certainly are well informed.
But the idea of that fake prince being\nthe Other is so WEIRD!
Yeah, don't these dolts even realize that\nthe Other is dead as a doornail?
Plus, there's no WAY a wuss like him\ncould ever be the Other! Kya ha ha ha!
Yeah, that phony couldn't even stand\nup to Nedrick, much less the Other!
So why does everyone believe it, then?
Because people everywhere labor under\nthe impression they are more intelligent\nthan they, in fact, are.
No one cares if information is correct.\nAll they care about is whether or not it fits\ntheir own preconceived notions.
And that is why they cannot discern the\ntruth of things and find themselves\nhopeless victims of deception.
Kya ha! Everyone is a puppet in the end!
But it DID start this fun little party,\nso I guess there's that!
So where should we go if we want to\nenjoy all of this fun, Ciella?
Oh, I imagine the most lively place\nwill be the Halidom.
That's where the fake prince lives!
If we go there, we might cross paths with\nthat wretched combat android.

The fake prince and the android alike seem
to be away now, but before long they ought
to return—and I doubt the reunion is going
to be a happy one for them.
A game of hide-and-seek will be starting\nbefore long, so I hope you two will be ＂it＂\nand find them.
Yessss! If I find that stupid android,\nI'm going to play TONS!
You certainly are fascinated by that one.\nBut as for me, it's time to take a look\nat that oh-so-serious Paladyn.
Looks like Ciella's gone. Say, Oto,\nlet's hurry and head for the Halidom!
Yes, let's. I can hardly wait!
This time, we're going to rip out that\n＂heart＂ of theirs and set them free!
